The paper deals with the practical implementation of free-space optical communication (FSO) systems using direct detection, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and optical physics (cs.OH). The paper also discusses the impact of turbulence on FSO systems, which falls under the category of networked systems (cs.NI). Additionally, the paper proposes a mode diversity scheme to improve the reliability of FSO systems, which can be considered as a signal processing technique (cs.PH) or a communication theory approach (cs.SI).
